```

Now we can combine `h3` and `h6`:
`|A - L| ≤ |B - A| + |B - L|`
`|B - A| + |B - L| ≤ |B - A| + |C - B| + |L - C|`
The first inequality is `h3`. The second inequality is `h6` (rearranged).
So, `|A - L| ≤ |B - A| + |C - B| + |L - C|`.

```tactics
linarith [h3, h6]
```

This completes the proof of the inequality. The final step is to use this inequality to conclude the proof.

The complete code block will be:
```tactics
exact h1
```
